author: Jasmine Dionne
text: Thank you for the connection, @RickiDOVE and thank you @CNN for allowing me to share my experience as a young, black woman whose #breastcancer was missed by a mammogram twice. https://t.co/TVQqBS2uiB  #bcsm

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: A lot of my breast cancer  advocacy work has been online, but @deebrown11 has me thinking about the importance of planting local roots as well. My head has been there lately so this is just confirmation. *Gears ⚙️ are turning.* #africanamericansmallbiz @JAXBIZtweets

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: I almost didn’t come to the #AfricanAmericanSmallBiz forum tonight. It was refreshing to hear successful entrepreneurs talk about overcoming fear and doubt, managing the day job and the dream job, and planning to succeed instead fearing things that haven’t happened yet.

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: It sounds so simple, but it’s easy to get overwhelmed by the sheer amount of tasks and challenges that arise as a small business owner. I love the idea of not just keeping a log, but tracking their urgency/importance from Darrin Eakins of @dublasewhiskey #africanamericansmallbiz

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: “For a testimony there has to be a test.” Kenny Gilbert talks about the importance of having a supportive partner as an entrepreneur. “WE” are in this together. #AfricanAmericanSmallBiz @JaxBizJournal

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: I appreciate how Lakita Spann of @mrpotatospread sees the attention from others as an opportunity to be held accountable instead allowing the fear of criticism to slow her down or control her moves. #AfricanAmericanSmallBiz @JaxBizJournal @JAXBIZtweets

author: Jasmine Dionne
text: This made my heart smile so much. 💓 The baby who said to buy ice cream and shoes if you’re mad is speaking my toxic love language. 😂 https://t.co/l0W2RgqshA
